=== Etymology ===
from Spanish meaning "hat" which in turn comes from Vulgar Latin "sub" meaning "under" and "umbra" meaning "shadow".

== [[noun]] ==
#a tall and wide rimmed hat made from felt or straw and usually worn in Mexico and the South Western U.S. Can be turned upside down and used as a receptacle for vomit or defecation after the consumption of Mexican food.
#a mixed drink with tequila, named after the Mexican hat.

